^B@2hondo717: Now let us discuss responding over 2@C. Most people these days play 22D as waiting, which means 2@D is almost automatic over 2@C, regardless of what responder has. The only time responder shows a suit is if they have a good suit. A good suit is defined as 5+ cards with at least two of the top 3 honors. So anne's 2@H bid was good, as she had a good heart suit. The only complication is that some people play that 2@H by responder shows a bust hand, no Aces or Kings. If you play that, then anne cannot bid 2@H. If 2@H shows a bust, then 2N is used by many to show hearts which is probably the best solution.|
